---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About | Adam Penn" description="The founder story: from software engineering to real estate, investing, and building for freedom.">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="page-header animate-in delay-1">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Bio with photo -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-2">
      <div class="bio-section">
        <img src="/headshot.jpg" alt="Adam Penn and girlfriend" class="bio-photo" />
        <div class="bio-text">
          <p>
            I'm Adam Penn, a founder, operator, and investor based in Northern California.
            I build businesses around real assets and run them with an engineering mindset:
            systems-first, data-driven, and built to last.
          </p>
          <p>
            I run <a href="https://bidwellcapitalfund.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bidwell Capital Fund</a>,
            <a href="https://pennproperties.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Penn Properties</a>,
            and co-host the <a href="http://wealthindependencepod.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wealth Independence Podcast</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Longer bio -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-3">
      <span class="section-label">The Longer Version</span>
      <div style="max-width: 560px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem;">
        <p>
          I studied Computer Science and started my career as a software engineer in Northern California.
          I enjoyed solving problems and building systems, but the desk job wasn't for me. Somewhere along the way,
          I started to feel the pull toward something more tangible and long-term. I wanted to build a legacy, not just a career.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2017, I put $23,000 into my first short-term rental. I always had a vision of owning 10 houses by the age of 30.
          I figured if I could debug software systems, I could figure out real estate operations. It turned out to be true, and more
          interesting than I expected. I used strategic debt and reinvested every gain. That one
          property became two, then five, then a multi-million-dollar portfolio, then a management company,
          then a syndication company with over $10,000,000 of investor capital raised.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today, my team and I manage 50+ rental units through Penn Properties, where we handle
          everything from guest experience to maintenance systems to revenue optimization.
          On the investment side, Bidwell Capital helps other investors access real asset strategies:
          real estate ownership, oil & gas working interests, and debt funds.
        </p>
        <p>
          The podcast started because I kept having the same conversations with friends in tech
          who wanted to invest but didn't know where to start beyond index funds.
          Dustin Bailey and I created Wealth Independence to share real frameworks,
          real case studies, and honest conversations about building passive income.
        </p>
        <p>
          The common thread across everything I do is simple: I believe in owning real assets,
          running disciplined operations, and building toward a life where your work and your
          freedom aren't in conflict. That's the game I'm playing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How I think -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-4">
      <span class="section-label">How I Think</span>
      <ul class="principles-list">
        <li>I focus on cash flow.</li>
        <li>I pair that with deals that have solid tax benefits.</li>
        <li>I utilize strategic debt.</li>
        <li>I set clear goals that aim me at my long-term vision.</li>
        <li>I execute daily on my goals.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Mantras -->
    <section class="section animate-in delay-5">
      <span class="section-label">Mantras</span>
      <ul class="principles-list">
        <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8-slO65mWE&t=262s" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Execute. Execute. Execute."</a> <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: 0.85rem;">Andy Frisella</span></li>
        <li>"I get out what I expect, so I choose to expect greatness." <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: 0.85rem;">Robert Helms</span></li>
        <li>"Pain is temporary. Quitting lasts forever." <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-size: 0.85rem;">Lance Armstrong</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
